author: The Current
description:
Watch Ruston Kelly describe his experience as a competitive figure skater
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Ruston Kelly’s new album, "Pale, Through the Window," released on Friday, Sept. 12, 2025, and just a few weeks later, Kelly visited The Current studio to play solo acoustic versions of songs from the new record — then later, he spoke with The Current's Zach McCormick, during which time Kelly reflected on his experience as a competitive figure skater. 

Ruston Kelly's 2025 album, "Pale, Through the Window," is available on @rounderrecords.

Credits

To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

Watch to see the full session of Thao and the Get Down Stay Down featuring previously unreleased footage, from when they visited The Current studio back in 2016.
